  "case_overview": {
    "headline": "Unknown 2024-10-24 price-manipulation incident",
    "what_happened": "On October 24, 2024, an attacker exploited an unverified Compound-like lending protocol on Base chain through price manipulation, draining approximately $1M in user funds. The attacker (0x7562846468089cf0e8f7b38ac53406b895284901) executed the attack via transaction 0x6ab5b7b51f780e8c6c5ddaf65e9badb868811a95c1fd64e86435283074d3149e.",
    "why_it_matters": "Unverified, unaudited lending deployments remain high-risk targets for price manipulation attacks. Compound forks inherit well-known oracle vulnerabilities that must be addressed through robust price feeds (e.g., Chainlink) and TWAP mechanisms. Users should avoid depositing funds into protocols lacking verified contracts and published audits.",
