  "exploit_path": {
    "summary": "The attacker targeted an unverified Compound-fork lending deployment on Base. Given the nature of price manipulation attacks against Compound-like protocols, the attacker likely manipulated the oracle price feed for a collateral asset, inflating its value to borrow significantly more assets than their collateral was worth. The unverified contract status indicates the protocol had not undergone proper security audits, leaving oracle vulnerabilities exposed. A proof-of-concept exploit was subsequently published in DeFiHackLabs, confirming the attack vector. The attack was executed in a single transaction, characteristic of flash loan-enabled price manipulation.",
